    <prp:abstract>From spectral decomposition for a complete sample of 1271 SDSS DR7 QSO spectra with z $&lt;$ 0.25, we have identified 26 recoiling SMBH candidates. We propose ALMA Band 6 HCN (3-2) \&amp; HCO$^+$ (3-2)observations to confirm whether kinamatically-identified recoiling SMBH candidates are a true recoiling SMBHs. Out of 26, 3 representative candidates are selected for this project. 
Detection of the recoiling SMBHs will have a significant astrophysical implications: it will solve scatter in the M-$\sigma$ relation, will give indirect evidence for the existence of gravitational wave, and will reveal hidden SMBH in the form of barebone and moving blackholes.</prp:abstract>
